- Tue 26 Feb 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=e40a2cdcce

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 25 Feb 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 875, of which 810 are confirmed and 65 are probable. In total, there have been 551 deaths (486 of confirmed and 65 of probable cases).
- 196 suspected cases under investigation;
- 3 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Mandima, 1 in Vuhovi and 1 in Butembo;
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 1 in Mandima, 1 in Vuhovi, and 1 in Butembo (all community deaths);
- 1 new recovery released from the Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Revision of databases
---------------------
- The different databases are being revised to check and harmonize them. In discussion with the different partners involved in epidemiological surveillance, the decision was made to reclassify all cases in the health zone where their symptoms of the disease started. Several questions arose as to the classification of some cases that had moved between 2 or even 3 health zones between the onset of symptoms and death. In these particular cases, only thorough investigations can determine where the person started to show signs of the disease, which may take several days. Pending the results of the investigations, some of these cases are tentatively classified in the health zone where they were detected.
- Among these cases, there is the patient from Katwa [North Kivu] who fled to Bunia [Ituri] with her family after falling ill in her area of residence but whose body was found in Komanda [Ituri]. This patient was initially classified in Komanda but was reclassified to the Katwa health zone after completion of the in-depth investigation.
- On Tue 26 Feb 2019, Lubero district [North Kivu] chief medical officer stated that a case of Ebola had been detected in the health zone of Lubero. This is a young woman from Katwa [North Kivu], who was known to be in contact with another confirmed case and who refused to be transferred to the Ebola treatment center when she became ill. She ran away from Katwa to Lubero. She died the next day at the Lubero General Referral Hospital from where the alert was launched. This patient was classified in the health zone of Katwa, where her 1st symptoms appeared.

Vaccination
-----------
Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 83 813 people have been vaccinated

