- Tue 26 Feb 2019. Lubero health zone
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni; in French, machine trans., edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5480

The health zone of Lubero [North Kivu] is the new health entity entering the Ebola epidemic. The confirmation was made on Mon 25 Feb 2019 by the chief doctor of the health zone. A confirmed case of Ebola has indeed died at the reference general hospital of Lubero. [See MoH report above] The response teams are deployed on-site to stop the threat.

The 1st action by the WHO and MSF team present at the Lubero General Referral Hospital is the dignified and secure burial of the confirmed fatal case. The funeral took place on the evening of Sat 23 Feb 2019 in Ngeleza, East of Lubero-Center. On Sun 24 Feb 2019, the team of health professionals proceeded to identify the 1st contacts of the victim. According to medical sources, at least 86 contacts were identified on Mon 25 Feb 2019. Our sources informed that vaccination of these 1st contacts -- those taking care of the deceased and the family members -- has started.

For the moment, the sensitization sessions have started at the Lubero-Center and all over the health zone. The Lubero health area is the 6th area affected by Ebola in the territory of Lubero.

